      <section xml:id="sec-intro-to-codap">
        <title>Introduction to CODAP</title>
        
        <p>
          CODAP (Common Online Data Analysis Platform) is a free, web-based data analysis tool designed specifically for educational purposes. It provides an intuitive interface for exploring data without requiring programming knowledge.
        </p>
        
        <subsection xml:id="subsec-codap-interface">
          <title>The CODAP Interface</title>
          
          <p>
            Let's explore the basic components of the CODAP interface:
          </p>
          
          <figure xml:id="fig-codap-interface">
            <caption>The CODAP Interface</caption>
            <image source="codap-interface.png" width="90%">
              <description>Screenshot of the CODAP interface showing the built-in Mammal example.</description>
            </image>
          </figure>
          
          <p>
            Key components include:
          </p>
          
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p><term>Tables</term>: Display data in rows and columns</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p><term>Graphs</term>: Create visual representations of data</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p><term>Calculator</term>: Perform calculations and create new attributes</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p><term>Map</term>: Plot geographic data</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p><term>Text</term>: Add explanatory notes to your document</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
          
            <p>
              You can access CODAP at <url href="https://codap.concord.org/" visual="codap.concord.org">codap.concord.org</url>. No login is required to get started, though you can save files to your local computer or link it to your Google drive, if you have one.
            </p>
        </subsection>
        
