      <section xml:id="sec-ethics-spotlight-data-collection">
        <title>Ethics Spotlight: Ethical Data Collection</title>
        
        <p>
          Before we conclude Unit 1, it's important to consider the ethical dimensions of data science. The data we collect and how we collect it has real impacts on people's lives.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Key ethical considerations in data collection include:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p><term>Consent</term>: Were people informed about how their data would be used?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><term>Privacy</term>: Is sensitive information protected?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><term>Representativeness</term>: Does the data collection process exclude certain groups?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><term>Transparency</term>: Is the collection process clear and documented?</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><term>Minimization</term>: Is only necessary data collected?</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
        
        <example xml:id="example-ethics-health">
          <statement>
            <p>
              In our Community Health dataset, consider these ethical questions:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <p>Are the neighborhoods defined in ways that might reinforce historical segregation?</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Does the dataset include communities that are often underrepresented in research?</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Is the aggregation level appropriate to protect individual privacy while still being useful?</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Were community members involved in deciding what data to collect about their neighborhoods?</p>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </statement>
        </example>
        
        <activity xml:id="activity-ethics-discussion">
          <title>Data Ethics Discussion</title>
          <introduction>
            <p>
              In this activity, we'll discuss ethical considerations for our datasets.
            </p>
          </introduction>
          <task>
            <statement>
              <p>
                For the Community Health dataset, identify at least two potential ethical concerns and how you might address them.
              </p>
            </statement>
          </task>
          <task>
            <statement>
              <p>
                For your chosen project dataset, consider:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <p>What was the original purpose of this data collection?</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Who collected it and how?</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Who might be missing from or underrepresented in this dataset?</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>Are there privacy concerns with this data?</p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </statement>
          </task>
        </activity>
      </section>

      <exercise xml:id="parsons-ethics-considerations" adaptive="yes">
        <title>Organizing Ethical Considerations</title>
        <statement>
          <p>Arrange the following steps in a logical order for ethically approaching a new dataset.</p>
        </statement>
        <blocks>
          <block order="3">
            <p>Evaluate how representative the dataset is of the population of interest.</p>
          </block>
          <block order="5">
            <p>Consider how results might be misinterpreted or misused.</p>
          </block>
          <block order="1">
            <p>Identify the original purpose and context of data collection.</p>
          </block>
          <block order="2">
            <choice>
              <p>Skip any ethical considerations to save time.</p>
            </choice>
            <choice correct="yes">
              <p>Determine if appropriate consent was obtained from data subjects.</p>
            </choice>
            <choice>
              <p>Immediately publish all raw data online for transparency.</p>
            </choice>
          </block>
          <block order="4">
            <p>Assess potential privacy concerns and identifiability of individuals.</p>
          </block>
          <block order="6" correct="no">
            <p>Use all data regardless of quality or ethical considerations.</p>
          </block>
        </blocks>
        <hint>
          <p>Think about what information you would need to know first before proceeding with analysis.</p>
        </hint>
      </exercise>

